    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-28T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="844"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d844">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Rumania)/7–2345:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 844<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Acting Representative in Rumania</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRM1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Melbourne</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract<note n="1" xml:id="d844fn1">For the full text
                            of this message, see <ref target="#d825">document No.
                        825</ref>.</note>]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-28T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 28, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>378. …</p>
                <p>. . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>… On the six articles mentioned in his<note n="2" xml:id="d844fn2">i. e.,
                            <persName corresp="#p_SBGCTVR1">Brigadier General
                        Schuyler</persName>’s.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_M1">M</gloss>–1285<note n="3" xml:id="d844fn3">See <ref
                            target="#d812">documents Nos. 812</ref> and <ref target="#d840"
                            >840</ref>.</note> his views are in general concurred in by <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>. We would not, however, regard any specific
                    protest on Article 7 as called for at the present time since Soviet Govt has
                    several times been apprised of this Govt’s position and matter is under
                    discussion at governmental level as part of question of defining <gloss
                        target="#t_War1">war</gloss> booty in all ex-enemy countries. …</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <lb/>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RS1">S[amuel] R[eber]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
